Hey everyone,<br>
<br>
       I've been away from the flame boards for quite some time, and I haven't givin much thought to comming back...until i got pissed in real life at something, and decided to share my little nugget of joy with the rest of ya'll. <br>
<br>
       So I checked through some old flames just to get caught back up, and I came across the post that said:<br>
<br>
&quot;christ,i think Balrak/Doofy/Boofy/or Thorsen need to write a HOW TO FLAME for DUMMIES Book&quot;<br>
<br>
GF Fantasm<br>
<br>
<br>
       So.....here I am. Basically, Drinals flame board sucks. I'm sure you all have valid flames and angers that you wish to express to the rest of us. And you should...many people find this enjoying, and comical. I for one love hearing, seeing, and even being a part of a flame. They give you attention, they make you more popular in EQ, and if your good, they can even give you a little respect.....that is if your really good.<br>
<br>
<br>
Topic 1 (creating a new flame)<br>
<br>
First off, the title.<br>
<br>
<br>
Make your flame interesting, but to the point. that way more people will be drawn into reading your flame.<br>
<br>
-try not to misspell any words in the title...<br>
....remember, you can always put (sp?) next to a word your aren't sure is correctly spelled.<br>
<br>
-Cuss words add to anger, especially the word (fuck)....try to use it often.<br>
-be creative in your title.<br>
.....if your calling someone a name, use words and phrases that aren't common....like decrepid anal wart, and bloody tampon fucker *theres a good way to add in the word (fuck)*<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Next we have the body of the flame. This is going to be the main focus of your flame. So when doing this part, you should always spend extra time on this. <br>
<br>
First most important thing in flaming, make sure to be creative. People hate reading a boring flame, and will even flame YOU for writing a bad flame, or misspelling a word. Take a look at all of Thoggs flames, and you'll catch the drift.<br>
<br>
Second, make sure you know what the hell your talking about. There is no easier target for a flame, then a person not knowing what they're talking about. Do some research, open a fucking book. *there's that (fuck) word again. <br>
<br>
Third, Adding illistrations to a flame can better add to a flame. Some times, all you need is a picture, and you know what they say... &quot;a pictures worth a thousand words&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
Here's my favorite:<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.legacyofsorrow.net/mj/threadgay.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
the easiest way to place a picture on a thread is to right click the picture from a web page, then type:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://enter web page here"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
When you are writing your flame, try not to leave any area's open where the flamed person can flame back....such as grammar, the length of your flame, and spelling of course.<br>
<br>
Make sure you don't accidentally offend any other people. Doing such a thing, can reverse the flame back onto you. *which can be fun*<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
And lastly....Ending a flame.<br>
<br>
<br>
Many people end flames in many different ways.<br>
<br>
<br>
Some will end it with a witty &quot;sig&quot;, others will just end it with &quot;fuck&quot; you, and some just won't end it.<br>
<br>
<br>
Often adding a picture can make the perfect ending to a flame. Such as calling someone a loser, then copy/pasting a picture from www.uglypeople.com<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
THE RULES OF FLAMING<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
1. Never ever ever assume that anyone really cares about your topic....cause they don't.<br>
<br>
2. Never start off a phrase with &quot;if I were you&quot;, or &quot;you know what I think?&quot;<br>
<br>
3. Don't take the flame boards serious, cause doing so will only give you a brain annurism(sp?)<br>
<br>
4. Bad things can, and will come from excessive use of the flame boards.<br>
<br>
5. Never bring up the issue of &quot;being cool&quot;, or &quot;having a life&quot; in a flame board. Cause lets face it....flaming an imaginary character, with your imaginary character isn't the text book definition of &quot;cool&quot;.<br>
<br>
6. Don't use AOL, don't make refrense to AOL, and NEVER say AOL is cool.<br>
<br>
7. Don't use age as a means of flaming someone, unless your going to be a little more creative about it....cause it's old, and it'll probably get you flamed as well.<br>
<br>
8. Don't over post...Don't Spam. <br>
    -Spam is an internet term for posting the same thing, or multiple things repeatedly, thus showing only what you have written, and nothing of what other people have writtin.<br>
<br>
    Spam will get you flamed, banned, and some junk.<br>
<br>
9. Pick topics you can relate to. <br>
    -Don't talk about sports, if the closest thing to sports you've ever done is flicking a paper triangle through a make shift field goal your friend made with his index fingers and thumbs.<br>
<br>
10. Know when to admit defeat. There is a boundary where a flame is good, and bad. It's a very fine line, and you should know when the tables have turned. DO NOT continue to fight your battle in the negative part of the boundary. Unless you wish to establish yourself as a prick, or a bitch....easiest thing to do is step out, let the flames die down, stay in eq, and build up your reputation again....then re-enter when the time is right.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
If you wish to add more, feel free to....this is merely a rough-draft of guidelines.<br>
<br>
Follow them, print this page, flame me, i don't give a (fuck)*.<br>
